class Solution {
public:
    int isPrefixOfWord(string sentence, string searchWord) {
        int n = sentence.length();
        int result = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (sentence.substr(i, searchWord.length()) == searchWord) {
                result = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates through the sentence character by character and checks if the substring of the sentence starting from the current index matches the searchWord. If a match is found, the index is stored as the result and the loop is terminated using the break statement. Since the sentence has at most n characters, the time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space to store the result and the searchWord.

